    "body": "### Problem\n\nCompletion menu overlaps the last character of statuscolumn.\n\n<img width=\"422\" height=\"680\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/988f0356-bb80-4e38-8396-c3e6731cc856\" />\n\nIn the image above, the completion menu overlaps the statuscolumn '|' character.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.o.number = true\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nvim.o.statuscolumn = \"%s%lâ”‚\"\n```\nAbove are the contents for init.lua file.\nOpen the init.lua file and in a newline between ``vim.o.number`` and ``vim.o.statuscolumn`` press <C-x><C-o> and you can see that the completion menu overlaps the '|' symbol thus hindering statuscolumn view.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCompletion menu should not hinder statuscolumn view.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1329+ga053186aa7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI dont use vim as of now so cannot confirm.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwsl2 archlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR neovim-git package",
