        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There are two ways for the completion menu to not overlap with the statuscolumn, but both may lead to worse UX:\n1. Move the popup menu by one cell to the left. But then the completion candidates won't be aligned with the inserted text.\n2. Remove the padding on the left. But then if the statuscolumn doesn't have padding on the right either, there will be no separation between text in the statuscolumn and text in the popup menu. This is not a GUI.\n\nTherefore I don't this behavior is worth changing.\n\n> Completion menu also does not overlap winbar and statusline.\n\nThis isn't correct. If you have a split window below, the popup menu can overlap with the current window's statusline. If you have a split window above and the current cursor position is close enough to the bottom of the screen, the popup menu can overlap with the current window's winbar.",
